VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT ^EXPOSE\s+\d+-\d{4,}|^EXPOSE\s+0\.0\.0\.0
WHEN EXPR MISSING:# intentional|# required|# documentation
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects EXPOSE instructions declaring broad port ranges or binding to all interfaces.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Broad Port Range Exposed.
